                            <comment id="13892526" author="tcame051" created="Wed, 5 Feb 2014 20:27:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My patch for the issue. I have repacked my jar with this fix and it is now working for me. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13892537" author="tilman" created="Wed, 5 Feb 2014 20:37:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;2.0.0 is also affected.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13893653" author="tilman" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2014 18:53:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I commited your change to revision 1565392 in the 2.0 version and 1565412 in the 1.8 version. I didn&apos;t use your exception handling because its already done &quot;above&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13893716" author="tcame051" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2014 19:49:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Great! Thanks for the quick response Tilman. I wasn&apos;t actually handling any exceptions, just guaranteeing that the stream was closed if an exception was thrown in one of those steps. I think this should be fine the way you committed it though. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
